reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Dr. Thompson explains complex concepts clearly. Her enthusiasm for math is contagious!

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Brilliant instructor. Prof. Chen's projects are challenging but incredibly rewarding.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Lectures can be dry, but Dr. Johnson's lab sessions are engaging and informative.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Prof. Martinez brings history to life with fascinating anecdotes and discussions.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Exceptional teacher. Dr. Lee's classes are thought-provoking and well-structured.

reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Brilliant mind, but Prof. Wilson struggles to explain concepts at an understandable level.

reviews.subject: Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Schmidt's passion for literature is evident. Her analysis of texts is insightful.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Prof. Taylor's lectures are informative, but his exams can be unnecessarily difficult.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Patel is an amazing educator. Her labs are well-organized and her explanations are crystal clear.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Thought-provoking lectures. Prof. Brown encourages critical thinking and lively debates.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Dr. Wong's research is interesting, but her teaching style can be a bit disorganized.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Prof. Kim's passion for art is infectious. His lectures are like guided tours through time.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Rodriguez brings real-world examples into the classroom, making the subject highly relevant.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Prof. Chang seems knowledgeable but often goes off-topic, making it hard to follow the course material.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Foster's field experience enriches her lectures. She makes anthropology fascinating and accessible.

reviews.subject: Engineering
reviews.review: Prof. Nguyen's practical approach to engineering problems is extremely helpful. Challenging but fair.

reviews.subject: Linguistics
reviews.review: Dr. White is knowledgeable, but her assignments can be vague and difficult to understand.

reviews.subject: Business
reviews.review: Prof. Green's real-world experience in business adds tremendous value to his classes. Highly recommended!

reviews.subject: Neuroscience
reviews.review: Dr. Clark simplifies complex neurological concepts. Her enthusiasm for the subject is contagious.

reviews.subject: Music Theory
reviews.review: Prof. Lee is a talented musician, but his teaching style can be a bit too abstract for beginners.
